1
00:00:03,253 --> 00:00:05,839
[theme music plays]

2
00:01:22,541 --> 00:01:28,463
GLARE

3
00:01:31,174 --> 00:01:34,261
That was footage from surveillance cameras
at the station.

4
00:01:34,469 --> 00:01:38,432
The death of one of the FBI agents
is captured on here. [groans]

5
00:01:38,849 --> 00:01:40,475
Let's see the following scenes again.

6
00:01:40,601 --> 00:01:42,978
Raye Penber passing the ticket gate
on his way in,

7
00:01:43,103 --> 00:01:46,064
then him boarding the train. And finally,
the part where he dies on the platform.

8
00:01:46,231 --> 00:01:47,274
[Shuichi Aizawa] Okay.

9
00:01:47,608 --> 00:01:48,609
Let's see…

10
00:01:48,775 --> 00:01:50,319
I think it's next to that.

11
00:01:51,028 --> 00:01:52,070
Oh, here it is.

12
00:01:52,529 --> 00:01:54,823
Um, so based on the records I have here,

13
00:01:55,032 --> 00:01:56,825
Raye Penber comes through
the west entrance

14
00:01:56,908 --> 00:01:59,494
of Shinjuku Station at 3:11 p.m.

15
00:02:00,162 --> 00:02:03,248
Then at 3:13 he boards a train
on the Yamanote Line.

16
00:02:03,415 --> 00:02:05,667
But even if he was following someone
at that time,

17
00:02:05,751 --> 00:02:08,879
I think it's going to be very difficult
for us to draw any real conclusions

18
00:02:09,046 --> 00:02:10,047
from this blurry video.

19
00:02:10,631 --> 00:02:13,216
And then at exactly 4:42 p.m. ...

20
00:02:14,051 --> 00:02:15,469
Oh, thank you very much, Watari.

21
00:02:16,261 --> 00:02:18,764
Um, and at 4:42 p.m.

22
00:02:18,889 --> 00:02:22,142
he exits the train at Tokyo station
and dies on the platform.

23
00:02:22,809 --> 00:02:24,394
It's quite strange, don't you think?

24
00:02:25,437 --> 00:02:27,481
I'm sorry, what do you find strange?

25
00:02:27,606 --> 00:02:29,274
Yeah, what is it?
Did you notice something?

26
00:02:31,026 --> 00:02:33,612
Mmm...
We know that Raye Penber got on the train

27
00:02:33,695 --> 00:02:36,740
and then an hour and a half later
he got off and died on the platform.

28
00:02:36,907 --> 00:02:39,743
But the Yamanote Line only takes an hour
to complete its circuit.

29
00:02:40,369 --> 00:02:42,162
And more importantly,
there's the envelope.

30
00:02:42,329 --> 00:02:43,622
-What do you mean?
-[remote beeps]

31
00:02:46,124 --> 00:02:48,001
[L] He's holding
what looks like an envelope

32
00:02:48,085 --> 00:02:49,503
when he passes through the ticket gate.

33
00:02:49,753 --> 00:02:51,004
[gasps] You're right.

34
00:02:51,254 --> 00:02:52,964
It's there, under his arm.

35
00:02:53,298 --> 00:02:56,510
But in the footage right before his death
it's gone!

36
00:02:56,760 --> 00:02:58,428
I can't believe you actually caught that.

37
00:02:59,763 --> 00:03:03,100
Well, I don't see an envelope
on this list of his personal effects.

38
00:03:03,433 --> 00:03:05,811
[L] Which means it was left in the train.

39
00:03:06,436 --> 00:03:08,730
And if you watch closely
at the very end here...

40
00:03:10,399 --> 00:03:12,859
it seems like he's straining
to look inside the train

41
00:03:12,943 --> 00:03:14,861
before the doors close.
You can see right here.

42
00:03:15,404 --> 00:03:17,656
If that's the case,
do you think it could mean something?

43
00:03:17,906 --> 00:03:20,450
Wouldn't it be interesting
if Kira was on that train?

44
00:03:20,575 --> 00:03:21,910
That's impossible!

45
00:03:22,285 --> 00:03:24,663
I admit I find it hard to believe as well.

46
00:03:25,247 --> 00:03:27,666
There's no reason for Kira
to come to the scene of his own crime

47
00:03:27,833 --> 00:03:29,334
when he can kill from a distance.

48
00:03:30,335 --> 00:03:33,964
Well... maybe he was counting on us
to make that assumption,

49
00:03:34,089 --> 00:03:36,466
and figured he could get away with
such a bold move.

50
00:03:44,307 --> 00:03:46,143
[Ryuk] What's going on with you, Light?

51
00:03:46,518 --> 00:03:49,271
You haven't stopped writing
criminals' names in the Death Note

52
00:03:49,396 --> 00:03:51,648
for four days straight.
So what are you trying to prove?

53
00:03:52,107 --> 00:03:55,193
I don't see the point in writing
these names weeks in advance.

54
00:03:55,277 --> 00:03:57,320
I've never seen the Death Note
used like this.

55
00:03:57,446 --> 00:03:58,864
Consider it insurance.

56
00:03:58,989 --> 00:04:02,033
Suppose the son of
the Detective Superintendent of the NPA

57
00:04:02,284 --> 00:04:05,078
was hospitalized,
if criminals stop dying at the same time

58
00:04:05,203 --> 00:04:06,997
it wouldn't be difficult
to connect the two.

59
00:04:07,456 --> 00:04:08,749
So that's what this is.

60
00:04:09,040 --> 00:04:10,834
Are you sure that I can use any date

61
00:04:10,959 --> 00:04:13,754
as long as it's before the end
of a person's predetermined lifespan?

62
00:04:14,337 --> 00:04:18,258
Well, I can't guarantee it, because
we Shinigami don't normally work that way.

63
00:04:18,925 --> 00:04:22,304
But I suppose any time before the end
of their lifespan should work.

64
00:04:23,346 --> 00:04:25,015
I really can't count on you, can I?

65
00:04:25,223 --> 00:04:26,349
You got that right.

66
00:04:27,184 --> 00:04:28,185
[Watari] Yes?

67
00:04:28,769 --> 00:04:30,562
Yes, would you please hold
for a moment.

68
00:04:30,812 --> 00:04:31,688
Ryuzaki.

69
00:04:32,355 --> 00:04:33,940
It's Ukita at the NPA.

70
00:04:34,357 --> 00:04:35,984
He says he's on the phone with someone

71
00:04:36,067 --> 00:04:38,153
from the tip-line
who has information for us.

72
00:04:38,361 --> 00:04:40,947
Right. Then give Ukita the number
for line five

73
00:04:41,072 --> 00:04:43,784
and ask him to have the informant
call that line instead.

74
00:04:43,867 --> 00:04:45,160
It'll be safer that way.

75
00:04:46,411 --> 00:04:49,372
Mr. Matsuda, it's okay for you
to turn on your cell phone now.

76
00:04:49,539 --> 00:04:51,208
Actually, please turn it on right away.

77
00:04:51,416 --> 00:04:52,459
Uh, sure.

78
00:04:54,085 --> 00:04:55,545
[phone rings]

79
00:04:55,879 --> 00:04:57,714
-[phone beeps]
-Yes, this is Suzuki,

80
00:04:57,798 --> 00:05:00,509
head of Kira's investigation
Public Information division.

81
00:05:01,676 --> 00:05:03,136
Raye Penber's fiancée?

82
00:05:03,887 --> 00:05:08,308
Naomi Misora...
I've heard that name before...

83
00:05:10,185 --> 00:05:11,144
[gasps]

84
00:05:11,645 --> 00:05:12,729
[L] So it's her.

85
00:05:12,854 --> 00:05:16,149
She from the Los Angeles BB murder case.
That's right!

86
00:05:16,608 --> 00:05:17,901
She was working under me.

87
00:05:18,610 --> 00:05:22,030
I guess she must have come to Japan
with her fiancée.

88
00:05:24,533 --> 00:05:25,408
[phone beeps]

89
00:05:25,951 --> 00:05:29,871
Well apparently she's been missing
since the day after her fiancé died.

90
00:05:30,288 --> 00:05:33,333
I'm sure that anyone in her situation
would be pretty depressed.

91
00:05:33,542 --> 00:05:35,669
Was it… suicide?

92
00:05:36,670 --> 00:05:39,464
No, the Naomi Misora I knew
was strong.

93
00:05:39,589 --> 00:05:42,551
Not to mention that she was also
an excellent FBI agent.

94
00:05:42,801 --> 00:05:46,096
If anything, it's more likely
that she'd be trying to catch Kira.

95
00:05:47,013 --> 00:05:49,015
It appears she came to Japan
with Penber.

96
00:05:49,641 --> 00:05:51,768
It's possible she may have found a lead.

97
00:05:52,686 --> 00:05:56,064
[L] If that's the case,
did Kira manage to get to her first?

98
00:05:57,524 --> 00:06:00,068
Everyone, from this point,
I'd like to focus our investigation

99
00:06:00,151 --> 00:06:02,654
on only those people
whom Raye Penber was tailing.

100
00:06:03,196 --> 00:06:04,114
In particular,

101
00:06:04,281 --> 00:06:08,660
he was assigned to two police officers
and those closest to them.

102
00:06:08,743 --> 00:06:11,329
Very well, who are these two individuals
he was investigating?

103
00:06:12,247 --> 00:06:15,709
Deputy Director General Kitamura,
along with…

104
00:06:16,001 --> 00:06:19,462
Detective Superintendent Yagami,
and their families.

105
00:06:19,921 --> 00:06:23,758
At this stage, I'd like to place wiretaps
and surveillance cameras

106
00:06:23,884 --> 00:06:25,385
in both households.

107
00:06:26,553 --> 00:06:29,306
[Light Yagami] I have to make there's
no evidence left on this computer.

108
00:06:29,431 --> 00:06:30,891
just in case someone goes through it.

109
00:06:33,768 --> 00:06:37,355
Now I just have to hide these clippings
from the Death Note in here.

110
00:06:38,648 --> 00:06:41,568
[Ryuk] It seems like you're pretty skilled
with your hands.

111
00:06:41,693 --> 00:06:44,154
I bet you're pretty popular
with the girls, aren't you?

112
00:06:44,446 --> 00:06:47,908
Skill has nothing to do with it.
It's your looks that count.

113
00:06:48,325 --> 00:06:50,827
I'm guessing you're not that popular,
are you?

114
00:06:51,161 --> 00:06:52,120
[Ryuk] Huh?

115
00:06:52,495 --> 00:06:54,664
[Touta Matsuda]
Surveillance cameras? Ryuzaki!

116
00:06:54,789 --> 00:06:56,917
[Aizawa] I don't see how
you could even consider this!

117
00:06:57,042 --> 00:06:59,461
If this got out, we'd have
a civil rights scandal on our hands.

118
00:06:59,628 --> 00:07:00,795
We'd all lose our jobs.

119
00:07:00,921 --> 00:07:03,715
You told me you'd be willing
to risk your lives for this investigation.

120
00:07:03,840 --> 00:07:05,091
But you wouldn't risk your jobs?

121
00:07:06,760 --> 00:07:09,763
Ryuzaki, what are the odds that Kira is
in one of those households?

122
00:07:11,348 --> 00:07:15,226
Maybe ten percent.
No, it's closer to five percent.

123
00:07:15,644 --> 00:07:16,561
Seriously?

124
00:07:16,770 --> 00:07:18,813
-Sorry, but it's not worth the risk.
-[Yagami] No.

125
00:07:18,897 --> 00:07:21,191
Of all the people
we've investigated so far,

126
00:07:21,358 --> 00:07:24,152
not one of them seemed
even the least bit suspicious.

127
00:07:24,527 --> 00:07:28,198
Even if there's only a one percent chance,
we simply can't afford to ignore it.

128
00:07:28,281 --> 00:07:29,282
[Matsuda] Chief!

129
00:07:29,449 --> 00:07:33,578
I don't have to tell you how offended I am
to learn my family is under suspicion.

130
00:07:33,870 --> 00:07:36,581
-Having said that, just go ahead with it.
-[both gasp]

131
00:07:36,998 --> 00:07:38,833
[Yagami] And make sure
you install them everywhere...

132
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:42,003
I don't want any blind spots in the house,
and that includes the bathroom.

133
00:07:42,963 --> 00:07:45,507
Thank you very much.
That was my intention.

134
00:07:45,757 --> 00:07:48,051
Come on, Chief.
You don't have to agree to this.

135
00:07:48,134 --> 00:07:50,011
Yes, he's right.
Think about your family.

136
00:07:50,178 --> 00:07:52,055
You have a wife
and daughter at home, don't you?

137
00:07:52,263 --> 00:07:54,015
Yes, I'm well aware of that fact.

138
00:07:54,391 --> 00:07:57,102
But there's no point in doing any of this
if we can't be thorough!

139
00:07:57,352 --> 00:07:58,979
Now I suggest you keep quiet.

140
00:07:59,437 --> 00:08:00,397
[both gasp]

141
00:08:02,899 --> 00:08:05,652
-[Matsuda] I'm sorry.
-No, it's okay.

142
00:08:06,027 --> 00:08:06,987
Excuse me.

143
00:08:09,364 --> 00:08:11,866
As a courtesy to the Chief and his family,

144
00:08:11,992 --> 00:08:14,953
only he and I will conduct surveillance
of their home.

145
00:08:15,578 --> 00:08:19,749
Watari, how long will it take to prepare
the wiretaps and cameras we need?

146
00:08:20,333 --> 00:08:21,668
Well, starting tomorrow,

147
00:08:22,043 --> 00:08:23,795
I can set them up at any time

148
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:26,172
provided we know when
both houses will be empty.

149
00:08:29,551 --> 00:08:30,760
[man] See you later, Light.

150
00:08:31,094 --> 00:08:32,595
Yeah, see you tomorrow.

151
00:08:36,224 --> 00:08:38,268
What? No one's home yet?

152
00:08:46,943 --> 00:08:48,194
I'm home.

153
00:08:57,162 --> 00:08:58,872
-[handle clicks]
-Huh?

154
00:09:00,040 --> 00:09:00,915
Hmm...

155
00:09:04,335 --> 00:09:05,253
[Ryuk] How's it going?

156
00:09:05,378 --> 00:09:07,589
I don't think anyone else is in
the house right now.

157
00:09:07,922 --> 00:09:09,674
Do you wanna play some video games?

158
00:09:11,301 --> 00:09:13,470
Come on, it's been awhile.

159
00:09:14,596 --> 00:09:15,722
Are you listening?

160
00:09:20,268 --> 00:09:21,269
Hey, Light?

161
00:09:27,859 --> 00:09:29,277
[Yagami] I don't believe it.

162
00:09:29,611 --> 00:09:31,738
I never knew he went
to such great lengths.

163
00:09:31,905 --> 00:09:35,241
What could he be hiding in there
that he doesn't want anyone else to see?

164
00:09:35,450 --> 00:09:38,286
For a 17-year-old kid,
I wouldn't say this kind of behavior

165
00:09:38,411 --> 00:09:39,871
is particularly abnormal.

166
00:09:40,497 --> 00:09:42,791
When I was his age,
I did strange things too.

167
00:09:43,333 --> 00:09:45,543
Have you ever talked to you son
about the investigation?

168
00:09:45,668 --> 00:09:46,628
Of course not!

169
00:09:46,711 --> 00:09:49,798
I've never once revealed
classified information to my family.

170
00:09:50,298 --> 00:09:53,176
Besides, I don't get to see them
too often these days,

171
00:09:53,384 --> 00:09:56,387
and usually as soon as I get home
all I can do is sleep.

172
00:09:56,513 --> 00:09:57,555
I understand.

173
00:09:58,973 --> 00:10:00,767
Where exactly are we going?

174
00:10:03,144 --> 00:10:05,480
Light, don’t ignore me
when I'm talking to you

175
00:10:05,563 --> 00:10:06,648
or I'll get mad.

176
00:10:08,650 --> 00:10:09,984
-[Light] Doesn't look ...
-[Ryuk] Hello!

177
00:10:10,110 --> 00:10:11,778
...like these clothes have been bugged.

178
00:10:11,945 --> 00:10:13,530
-Yoo-hoo!
-[Light] I think we're safe.

179
00:10:13,822 --> 00:10:14,697
Listen to me.

180
00:10:14,781 --> 00:10:17,367
There's a very strong possibility
that there are wiretaps,

181
00:10:17,492 --> 00:10:20,620
and maybe even surveillance cameras,
hidden throughout my house.

182
00:10:20,912 --> 00:10:24,457
Really? But that piece of paper
was still in your door, wasn't it?

183
00:10:24,999 --> 00:10:27,836
-That's true, but...
-I left the paper in the door in a way

184
00:10:27,919 --> 00:10:29,963
that it would be obvious
to anyone entering the room.

185
00:10:30,213 --> 00:10:32,549
-The real test is the handle.
-It is?

186
00:10:33,174 --> 00:10:34,175
When that door is closed,

187
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:36,845
the door handle automatically returns
to a horizontal position

188
00:10:36,928 --> 00:10:38,555
and it won't go any higher than that.

189
00:10:39,013 --> 00:10:41,516
But whenever I close the door,
I adjust it slightly.

190
00:10:41,724 --> 00:10:45,562
Instead of letting it sit horizontally,
I lower it by about five millimeters.

191
00:10:45,895 --> 00:10:48,815
When I get home and try to open the door,
if the handle is all the way up,

192
00:10:48,982 --> 00:10:51,526
I can be fairly certain
that someone was in my room.

193
00:10:52,652 --> 00:10:55,780
But that method alone doesn't tell me
if my door was actually opened.

194
00:10:56,281 --> 00:10:59,033
So I also put a mechanical
pencil lead in place as well.

195
00:10:59,367 --> 00:11:00,660
So what do you do with it?

196
00:11:00,994 --> 00:11:02,412
It goes on the hinge.

197
00:11:02,704 --> 00:11:03,788
After I close the door,

198
00:11:03,872 --> 00:11:05,999
I take the pencil lead
and rest it on the hinges

199
00:11:06,124 --> 00:11:09,252
in such a way that it will break if
the door happens to be opened by anyone.

200
00:11:09,377 --> 00:11:12,088
Normally I take it out myself
when I get back home.

201
00:11:12,547 --> 00:11:13,965
When I got home from school today,

202
00:11:14,090 --> 00:11:16,217
I noticed that the pencil lead was broken.

203
00:11:16,384 --> 00:11:18,761
Now that you mention it,
I do remember that.

204
00:11:19,053 --> 00:11:20,471
First the door handle,

205
00:11:20,597 --> 00:11:23,016
then the lead.
I know someone was in there today.

206
00:11:23,266 --> 00:11:24,684
Maybe it was your mother.

207
00:11:25,101 --> 00:11:27,604
My family wouldn't have noticed
the piece of paper.

208
00:11:27,687 --> 00:11:31,107
What's suspicious is that someone
took the time to put it back in the door.

209
00:11:31,274 --> 00:11:32,275
PSYCHOLOGY
PSYCHOTHERAPY

210
00:11:32,358 --> 00:11:33,484
[woman] Hi there, can I help you?

211
00:11:33,860 --> 00:11:35,862
What's this all about?
Are you buying a book

212
00:11:35,987 --> 00:11:38,656
about wiretaps and surveillance
so you can figure this mess out?

213
00:11:38,781 --> 00:11:39,699
SHOGEN BOOKS

214
00:11:40,950 --> 00:11:43,453
By the way, Ryuk,
what about your apples?

215
00:11:44,245 --> 00:11:45,121
Apples?

216
00:11:45,747 --> 00:11:48,708
Oh! That's right, surveillance cameras.

217
00:11:49,167 --> 00:11:51,836
Once the apple's in my mouth,
no one can see it.

218
00:11:52,003 --> 00:11:54,422
But while I'm holding it,
it looks like it's floating.

219
00:11:54,547 --> 00:11:55,506
[Light] I thought so.

220
00:11:55,924 --> 00:11:58,176
You told me that Shinigami can't die,

221
00:11:58,426 --> 00:12:01,137
so I guess it won't kill you
to stop eating apples for a while.

222
00:12:01,304 --> 00:12:03,890
[grumbles] Don't you think
that's a bit much? Come on.

223
00:12:03,973 --> 00:12:06,392
I never told you this,
but apples are to me

224
00:12:06,601 --> 00:12:10,188
what cigarettes and alcohol are to humans.
Do you see what I'm saying?

225
00:12:10,438 --> 00:12:12,732
I even get withdrawal symptoms.

226
00:12:12,941 --> 00:12:14,776
[Light] Oh yeah?
What kind of symptoms?

227
00:12:15,193 --> 00:12:18,488
My body gets all twisted.
I do handstands. It's not pretty!

228
00:12:18,613 --> 00:12:20,615
-I don't want to see that.
-I know.

229
00:12:21,199 --> 00:12:22,659
Okay, here's the thing.

230
00:12:23,034 --> 00:12:26,120
Unfortunately, I already gave L the hint
that Shinigami love apples,

231
00:12:26,287 --> 00:12:27,997
so I just can't afford
to take the risk.

232
00:12:28,164 --> 00:12:29,332
When did you…

233
00:12:30,124 --> 00:12:32,168
If it's so important for you
to eat apples...

234
00:12:34,295 --> 00:12:37,131
you'll have to find out
where all the cameras are hidden.

235
00:12:37,257 --> 00:12:39,175
If you're lucky,
you might find a blind spot

236
00:12:39,259 --> 00:12:41,010
where you can eat them
without being seen.

237
00:12:41,886 --> 00:12:43,805
All right, let's go!

238
00:12:44,681 --> 00:12:46,557
Yeah! the camera search.

239
00:12:47,725 --> 00:12:50,228
[Ryuk] Sounds so interesting.

240
00:13:17,297 --> 00:13:20,341
Oh, uh... I have to find the cameras.

241
00:13:21,384 --> 00:13:24,387
I can't believe my son is looking at
those magazines.

242
00:13:25,388 --> 00:13:27,140
It's normal for a 17-year-old.

243
00:13:28,099 --> 00:13:29,934
But it seems contrived.

244
00:13:30,268 --> 00:13:31,436
It's too obvious.

245
00:13:31,519 --> 00:13:33,855
The only reason he didn't want anyone
in his room

246
00:13:33,980 --> 00:13:36,649
was because he had these magazines?
That's what he wants us to think.

247
00:13:36,774 --> 00:13:38,651
Hey, that's my son
you're talking about.

248
00:13:39,027 --> 00:13:41,279
Are you honestly telling me
that you suspect him?

249
00:13:41,696 --> 00:13:43,031
I do suspect him.

250
00:13:43,489 --> 00:13:46,200
That's why I placed wiretaps
and surveillance cameras in your house

251
00:13:46,284 --> 00:13:47,785
and the Deputy Director's house.

252
00:13:48,703 --> 00:13:49,579
Huh?

253
00:13:50,079 --> 00:13:52,081
I found a camera in the air conditioner.

254
00:13:52,206 --> 00:13:53,082
[Light] Hm.

255
00:13:53,750 --> 00:13:55,543
So, they really put cameras
in here.

256
00:13:55,793 --> 00:13:57,628
They must have bugged the place
as well.

257
00:13:58,254 --> 00:13:59,589
Even if this is the Kira case,

258
00:13:59,756 --> 00:14:02,175
I didn't think the Japanese police
would ever go this far.

259
00:14:02,925 --> 00:14:04,177
This must be L's idea.

260
00:14:04,385 --> 00:14:06,888
Which means they've narrowed down
their list of suspects.

261
00:14:07,263 --> 00:14:09,223
By now they must have figured out
that it was someone

262
00:14:09,307 --> 00:14:10,475
who Raye Penber was investigating,

263
00:14:10,558 --> 00:14:12,352
or they wouldn't have gone to
all this trouble.

264
00:14:12,435 --> 00:14:13,311
[Ryuk] Huh...

265
00:14:16,522 --> 00:14:18,858
Man, these covers mislead you
all the time.

266
00:14:19,984 --> 00:14:20,943
No...

267
00:14:21,110 --> 00:14:24,864
Given the situation, it's safer if
I just assume I'm their prime suspect,

268
00:14:24,989 --> 00:14:26,616
and the only one being watched.

269
00:14:27,033 --> 00:14:28,409
It'll be okay.

270
00:14:28,659 --> 00:14:31,329
Luckily I prepared for
this kind of situation.

271
00:14:35,416 --> 00:14:36,709
Oh, Light…

272
00:14:37,627 --> 00:14:41,964
Hey, Light!
Come on, dinner's ready.

273
00:14:43,883 --> 00:14:45,093
[man on TV] I love you.

274
00:14:45,593 --> 00:14:46,636
Always.

275
00:14:49,347 --> 00:14:50,181
[sighs]

276
00:14:52,266 --> 00:14:55,186
Hideki Ryuga.
I swear he's perfect.

277
00:14:55,395 --> 00:14:57,814
How come no one in my class
is like that?

278
00:14:58,147 --> 00:15:00,358
Sayu, just eat your dinner.

279
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:02,110
[Sayu Yagami] I'll eat later!

280
00:15:02,360 --> 00:15:05,780
Hello, Mr. Aizawa? Are the Kitamuras
watching television now?

281
00:15:05,863 --> 00:15:06,781
[Aizawa] Yes.

282
00:15:07,073 --> 00:15:10,076
He's not home, but the other four
are watching while they eat dinner.

283
00:15:10,410 --> 00:15:11,702
It's channel four.

284
00:15:12,870 --> 00:15:16,624
Watari, please contact the broadcasters
and tell them to play our message.

285
00:15:16,833 --> 00:15:18,209
[Watari] Very well.

286
00:15:18,584 --> 00:15:19,627
NKK NEWS FLASH

287
00:15:19,752 --> 00:15:21,712
[Sayu] Huh? What this?

288
00:15:22,588 --> 00:15:24,590
The ICPO?
They're saying that...

289
00:15:24,715 --> 00:15:26,426
"In response to the Kira murders,

290
00:15:26,717 --> 00:15:30,263
Interpol has decided to dispatch a force
of 1500 investigators to Japan.

291
00:15:30,471 --> 00:15:33,015
The investigators were drawn from
the law enforcement agencies

292
00:15:33,182 --> 00:15:34,225
of its member nations.

293
00:15:35,017 --> 00:15:37,061
Fifteen hundred investigators

294
00:15:37,353 --> 00:15:38,312
Woah!

295
00:15:39,313 --> 00:15:42,024
[Light] Chances are they've got cameras
in the living room as well.

296
00:15:42,150 --> 00:15:44,569
Regardless of whether
this news is real or not,

297
00:15:44,694 --> 00:15:47,447
it's obvious they're just trying to evoke
a reaction from me.

298
00:15:47,989 --> 00:15:51,409
L, it's the exact same trick
you used last time.

299
00:15:52,535 --> 00:15:55,037
-The ICPO sure is stupid.
-Huh?

300
00:15:55,705 --> 00:15:57,957
I mean, there's no point
in making this announcement.

301
00:15:58,374 --> 00:16:00,793
If they're going to send
all these people here to investigate

302
00:16:00,877 --> 00:16:02,462
shouldn't they keep it a secret?

303
00:16:03,045 --> 00:16:06,799
Even the FBI agents who were secretly
investigating were killed by Kira.

304
00:16:07,008 --> 00:16:08,551
Why would this be any different?

305
00:16:08,718 --> 00:16:11,262
If you ask me, this is nothing more than
a desperate attempt

306
00:16:11,345 --> 00:16:14,056
to shock Kira, in the hopes that
he'll reveal himself somehow.

307
00:16:14,182 --> 00:16:17,018
Quite frankly, I wouldn't be surprise
if Kira sees right through this.

308
00:16:18,060 --> 00:16:19,228
[chuckles quietly]

309
00:16:20,021 --> 00:16:22,023
Your son is clever, isn't he?

310
00:16:22,315 --> 00:16:24,108
Huh. Well, yes.

311
00:16:24,442 --> 00:16:26,152
[Light] Thanks for dinner, Mom.

312
00:16:26,527 --> 00:16:28,654
[Sayu] Huh?
You're eating a bag of chips?

313
00:16:28,779 --> 00:16:29,697
You just had dinner!

314
00:16:29,780 --> 00:16:32,283
Your looks will go
if you keep that up.

315
00:16:32,408 --> 00:16:34,410
It's a late-night snack for studying.

316
00:16:37,955 --> 00:16:39,332
I think that's it, Light.

317
00:16:39,749 --> 00:16:42,084
I found every camera
they put in the house.

318
00:16:42,376 --> 00:16:45,338
I guess even Shinigami get tired
when they work hard.

319
00:16:45,630 --> 00:16:47,715
Now let me explain where they all are.

320
00:16:48,132 --> 00:16:50,593
It's a little bit complicated,
so listen up.

321
00:16:50,843 --> 00:16:53,804
There's nothing I hate more
than explaining something twice.

322
00:16:54,055 --> 00:16:55,973
[Light] All right, time for me
to hit the books.

323
00:16:57,058 --> 00:16:59,519
[Ryuk] There sure are
a lot of cameras in this room.

324
00:16:59,602 --> 00:17:01,771
I counted 64 in total.

325
00:17:02,021 --> 00:17:05,608
I guess whoever put them here
expected you'd at least find some of them.

326
00:17:06,025 --> 00:17:07,527
[Light] It has to be L.

327
00:17:07,610 --> 00:17:10,696
He had no qualms about putting
a death row inmate in his place

328
00:17:10,780 --> 00:17:12,281
when he declared war on me.

329
00:17:12,698 --> 00:17:14,742
It's pretty clear he doesn't know
any limits.

330
00:17:15,076 --> 00:17:18,704
Ugh. What I want to know is,
how am I going to be able to eat apples?

331
00:17:18,996 --> 00:17:20,998
[Light] Obviously that's impossible now,
isn't it?

332
00:17:21,415 --> 00:17:24,293
Oh, yeah, I guess you can't talk in here.

333
00:17:24,544 --> 00:17:27,046
But we better discuss this
outside tomorrow.

334
00:17:27,547 --> 00:17:30,049
Okay, I think I'm getting
the hang of this now.

335
00:17:30,967 --> 00:17:33,135
[Light] Judging from the number of cameras
he's planted,

336
00:17:33,261 --> 00:17:35,888
he's planning to make a decision
within a short period of time.

337
00:17:36,639 --> 00:17:39,559
Any normal person would slip
under these circumstances,

338
00:17:39,642 --> 00:17:41,894
but it won't be that easy with me, L.

339
00:17:42,311 --> 00:17:44,689
This is the closest you will get!

340
00:17:50,403 --> 00:17:52,697
[Ryuk chuckles]

341
00:17:58,619 --> 00:18:01,247
[Light] I've set things up so that
criminals will continue to die

342
00:18:01,330 --> 00:18:02,540
over the next three weeks.

343
00:18:02,957 --> 00:18:06,919
L is aware by now that Kira can control
the times of death of his victims.

344
00:18:07,378 --> 00:18:08,963
Therefore, to avoid suspicion,

345
00:18:09,171 --> 00:18:11,799
L needs to see criminals
whose names are being broadcast

346
00:18:11,882 --> 00:18:15,011
continue to die while I have no access
to that information.

347
00:18:15,720 --> 00:18:16,596
Oh!

348
00:18:17,013 --> 00:18:18,889
The symptoms are starting.

349
00:18:19,432 --> 00:18:21,517
[Light] I'm going to show you, L!

350
00:18:26,564 --> 00:18:29,400
With Ryuk's information
and my preparations,

351
00:18:29,650 --> 00:18:32,987
I can continue to kill criminals
whose names are broadcast on the news,

352
00:18:33,529 --> 00:18:36,282
while masquerading as
as a typical high school student

353
00:18:36,365 --> 00:18:38,367
studying for his entrance exams.

354
00:18:39,201 --> 00:18:40,620
Just watch me, L.

355
00:18:40,786 --> 00:18:43,873
I'll solve equations with my right hand
and write names with my left.

356
00:18:44,040 --> 00:18:44,874
MURAO TA....

357
00:18:44,957 --> 00:18:46,375
SUSPECT: TAYOSHI MURAO

358
00:18:46,917 --> 00:18:50,838
[Light] I'll take a potato chip...
and eat it!

359
00:19:01,807 --> 00:19:04,101
[L] After dinner,
your son just goes back to studying

360
00:19:04,226 --> 00:19:06,395
without turning on
the TV or his computer.

361
00:19:06,771 --> 00:19:09,690
It's because the entrance exams
are five days away.

362
00:19:19,450 --> 00:19:22,870
[Light] Now, a criminal
who I should have no knowledge of

363
00:19:23,037 --> 00:19:25,414
will die of a heart attack
in forty seconds.

364
00:19:26,248 --> 00:19:30,294
And the witness to my alibi is L himself.

365
00:19:34,715 --> 00:19:36,550
All right, just a little bit longer!

366
00:19:42,473 --> 00:19:43,641
Ryuzaki.

367
00:19:43,849 --> 00:19:45,101
What is it, Watari?

368
00:19:45,768 --> 00:19:46,894
A few minutes ago,

369
00:19:46,977 --> 00:19:49,480
a bank clerk being questioned
on suspicion of embezzlement,

370
00:19:49,563 --> 00:19:52,274
and a purse-snatcher
being held in a detention center

371
00:19:52,608 --> 00:19:54,110
were broadcast on the news...

372
00:19:54,276 --> 00:19:57,655
They both just died of sudden,
inexplicable heart attacks.

373
00:19:58,322 --> 00:19:59,740
It's him again!

374
00:20:00,157 --> 00:20:02,201
While all that was happening at your home,

375
00:20:02,284 --> 00:20:04,704
your wife and daughter
were watching television.

376
00:20:05,329 --> 00:20:09,083
When that was over, they turned the TV off
and didn't watch anything afterwards.

377
00:20:09,792 --> 00:20:12,628
From just past seven thirty
until now, eleven o'clock,

378
00:20:12,712 --> 00:20:14,422
your son's done nothing but study.

379
00:20:14,839 --> 00:20:18,134
Kira needs a name and a face.
Without those, he can't kill.

380
00:20:18,801 --> 00:20:22,722
So I suppose anyone who didn't watch
the news can't be Kira, right?

381
00:20:23,097 --> 00:20:25,975
You said it yourself, that means
my family has been cleared.

382
00:20:26,392 --> 00:20:29,603
It doesn't make sense
that Kira would kill two petty criminals

383
00:20:29,687 --> 00:20:31,897
right after
their identities were broadcast.

384
00:20:32,064 --> 00:20:33,357
[Yagami gasps]

385
00:20:33,482 --> 00:20:36,360
I know it's only the first day
after the cameras were installed,

386
00:20:36,444 --> 00:20:39,071
but the Yagami household seems
almost too innocent to me.

387
00:20:39,697 --> 00:20:40,656
Hmm...

388
00:20:43,951 --> 00:20:45,995
[Light's mom]
Light, are you up yet?

389
00:20:46,829 --> 00:20:48,372
[Light] Yeah, I'm awake.

390
00:20:48,956 --> 00:20:52,126
Today is garbage day, so if you've got
any, bring it down with you, okay?

391
00:20:53,043 --> 00:20:54,420
[Light] What a pain!

392
00:20:54,545 --> 00:20:56,547
[Light's mom]
What are you talking about?

393
00:20:56,672 --> 00:20:59,550
You usually say,
"There's no need to remind me, Mom."

394
00:21:00,342 --> 00:21:01,510
[Light] Yeah, yeah…

395
00:21:04,305 --> 00:21:05,306
[groans]

396
00:21:06,474 --> 00:21:07,850
Another beautiful day.

397
00:21:08,017 --> 00:21:11,687
Well, I can't say for sure
whether you're extremely generous

398
00:21:11,771 --> 00:21:13,397
or just a spoiled brat.

399
00:21:13,856 --> 00:21:17,777
But didn't that mini-LCD TV cost you
400 bucks?

400
00:21:20,946 --> 00:21:22,406
[Light's mom] Good morning.

401
00:21:30,456 --> 00:21:36,462
TO BE CONTINUED

402
00:21:41,884 --> 00:21:46,806
[theme music plays]
